page.title: 20CONCLUSION TO SURVEY
page.content: Class 4 at Aldborough County primary school have done the work for the Domesday project.They have all enjoyed the research and it has helped them make greater use of the computer in school.Here is a list of the children in the class:Suzanne Owen,Adell Ward, Abigail Oliver,Theresa O'callaghan, Samantha Mears,Victoria Haviland,Kate Allen,Claire Davison,Beverley Craske, Angela Biss,Anna Langford,Lucy Sharpe, Claire Cushing,Natalie Turner,Richard Poynton,James Goff,Reuben Wragg,James Nisbet,Kenneth Spooner,Marc Shaw,Clive Thorne,Daniel Barrett,Fergus Mcfarland ,Nicholas Isaacs,Kevin Davison,Daniel Thomas,Alexander Fidgen. They have been greatly helped by their parents and naghbors and have been encouraged by other members of staff at school.Thank you to everyone-they hope people will find it interesting.
